Wikis en educación
Si ya hace días hablábamos del uso de <a href="http://fernand0.blogalia.com//historias/21108">bitácoras en educación</a>, y el otro día hablábamos de wikis en <a href="http://fernand0.blogalia.com/historias/21968">wikis y bitácoras</a>, convendrá ahora señalar el artículo <a href="http://www.educause.edu/pub/er/erm04/erm0452.asp">Wide Open Spaces: Wikis, Ready or Not</a>. Me gustan especialmente las citas seleccionadas:

<blockquote>
Making the simple complicated is commonplace; making the complicated simple, awesomely simple, that's creativity.
Charles Mingus
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
A wiki in the hands of a healthy community works. A wiki in the hands of an indifferent community fails. The software makes no attempt to add `process' in order to keep people from doing stupid things 
Clay Shirky
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
Please, grant me the serenity to accept the pages I cannot edit, The courage to edit the pages I can, And the wisdom to know the difference 
The Wiki Prayer
</blockquote>

